# Line-ending normalization. core.autocrlf=true was handing Windows checkouts
# CRLF, which breaks prettier (endOfLine=lf) and made the husky pre-commit
# format check fail locally — so commits bypassed the gate and Rust/format
# issues reached CI. The repo stores LF; enforce LF in every working tree so
# local checks match CI on all platforms.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary assets: never apply text or EOL filters. (.svg is XML — left as text.)
*.png  binary
*.ico  binary
*.icns binary
